{
    "name": "Lashunta",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any (Castrovel)<br/><b>Organization</b> any<br/><b>Treasure</b> NPC gear (light crossbow with 20 bolts, quarterstaff, gold amulet [bonded object], other treasure)"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The lashunta are the primary race of Castrovel, called \u201cthe Green Planet\u201d for its steaming jungles. Though the women look like idealized elves or humans\u2014save for the twitching antennae sprouting from their foreheads\u2014their men are squat, hairy, and broad-shouldered, with a fierce and confrontational demeanor. Both genders excel at scholarship, and the race boasts a large number of telepaths and telekinetics, in addition to conventional magic-users. This ability to create mental or empathic bonds is particularly prevalent among female warriors, who form close connections with their saurian mounts.<br/><br/>Female lashunta are typically 6 feet tall and weigh 140 pounds. The males of the race are usually 5 feet tall and weigh 200 pounds."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>Delicate antennae extend from the forehead of this lithe woman.</i>",
